      "content": "Modern historians often view the UN's effectiveness with considerable nuance, suggesting mixed results rather than outright failure or consistent success. While the UN has been crucial in humanitarian aid, peacekeeping missions, and preventing several localized conflicts from escalating, its ability to stop major, state-backed wars is often hampered by veto power among permanent members. Therefore, many scholars argue it is a vital tool for international diplomacy, but not an infallible guarantor of global peace.",
